   <mods:abstract>A potentially dangerous political situation in Europe may be fanned into
            flames by the erratic actions of England. Republican group in Holland is losing ground
            and cannot agree upon a general. If war comes he believes that United States should
            avoid engagement because she is ill prepared for a new conflict, and she can best aid
            France by remaining neutral. This would be a good time to try to obtain restoration of
            the navigation of the Mississippi. All in Europe anxiously await the results of the
            Philadelphia convention.</mods:abstract>
